'''''Dorsum''''' (pl. '''''dorsa''''') is a [[Latin]] word used by [[planetary geology|planetary geologists]] to refer to [[ridge]]s on the surfaces of [[planet]]s and [[natural satellite|moon]]s.

''See also:'' [[wrinkle-ridge]].

